                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24596/12–1846: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">McNutt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 18, 1946—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>867. War has temporarily suspended construction contracts Phils. Heavy expense
                    involved such suspensions which cannot be maintained this status indefinitely.
                    As decision on resumption all or part depends on request PhilGovt re
                    continuation American forces War requests you be apprised urgency early decision
                    this point.</p>
                <p>If decision this point not promptly made will be necessary cancel contracts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
